snippet.title: Maria Gaetana Agnesi
snippet.description: In 1738 she published a collection of complex essays on natural science and philosophy called Propositiones Philosophicae, based on the discussions of the intellectuals who gathered at her father's home. After the success of her book, Maria was elected to the Bologna Academy of Sciences.
